# Since I can't directly create Excel files, I'll create a CSV that can be converted to Excel
# This shows the expected structure for Excel rule files

# Option 1: Single Sheet Format
# Column headers: func, mutation, default_severity, notes, inplace_critical, library, alias_regex

func,mutation,default_severity,notes,inplace_critical,library,alias_regex
custom_delete,data deletion,HIGH,Custom function that deletes data,FALSE,custom,^(custom|cust)$
custom_update,data update,MEDIUM,Updates data in place,TRUE,custom,^(custom|cust)$
risky_transform,data transformation,HIGH,Transforms data in a risky way,FALSE,custom,^(custom|cust)$
hardcoded_number,hardcoded number,CRITICAL,Flags hardcoded numeric values,FALSE,custom,^(custom|cust)$

# Option 2: Multi-Sheet Format would have:
# Sheet 1 "meta": 
#   Column A: library, Column B: custom
#   Column A: alias_regex, Column B: ^(custom|cust)$
#
# Sheet 2 "rules":
#   func | mutation | default_severity | notes | inplace_critical
#   custom_delete | data deletion | HIGH | Custom function that deletes data | FALSE
#   custom_update | data update | MEDIUM | Updates data in place | TRUE
#   hardcoded_number | hardcoded number | CRITICAL | Flags hardcoded numeric values | FALSE 